b'' b'' b'' b'it is a good idea to include at least:' b'openwindows.focuslenience:\ttrue' b'*input: true' b'in your .xdefaults file, as these allow non-icccm-compliant programs to' b'receive input even if they forget to ask for it.' b'see the next item for editing .xdefaults' b'' b'' b'under openwindows you need to add the following either to your' b'$home/.xdefaults file, or to $openwinhome/lib/app-defaults/xterm instead:' b'' b'xterm*vt100.translations: #override b'<keyl6:select-set(clipboard)\\n\\' b'<keyl8:insert-selection(clipboard)' b'' b'you must not move the mouse between ending the selection and pressing' b'l8 (the paste key)!' b'' b'under openwindows this is already in the app-defaults file, so if it' b"isn't working, check that xfilesearchpath is set to" b'/usr/openwin/lib/%t/%n%s' b"and if it isn't, either set it or copy/merge the above lines from" b'$openwinhome/lib/app-defaults/xterm into /usr/lib/x11/app-defaults/xterm.' b'[see also: environment variables]' b'' b'this version automatically puts each xterm selection onto the clipboard:' b'xterm*vt100.translations: #override\\n\\' b'~ctrl ~meta<btn2up: insert-selection(primary,cut_buffer0)\\n\\' b'~ctrl ~meta<btnup: select-end(primary,cut_buffer0,clipboard)\\n\\' b'<keypressl8: insert-selection(clipboard)' b'[note: be sure that the \\n\\ is at the very end of the line, there must' b'be no following spaces, and any or signs showing that this faq file' b'was altered must also be removed!]' b'' b'if you are using x11r5, you may find that adding the lines' b'<keyl10: start-extend() select-end(primary, clipboard, cut_buffer0)\\n\\' b'<keyreleasel10: kill-selection() \\n' b'before the <keypressl8 line will make l10 (cut) work as a cut key!' b'' b'if you alter $home/.xdefaults instead, you must use what x calls a' b"`more specific' resource name:" b'xterm.vt100.translations' b'will do.' b'' b'' b"if you don't have the sun l keys on the left of your keyboard, you can" b'use meta-x, meta-c and meta-v for cut, co